### Part B — Offline vs Online Methods

#### Offline Methods

Traditional face-to-face methods. Still dominant in most Indian universities.

**Face-to-face lecture** — The default mode in colleges. Has the advantage of real-time Q&A, non-verbal communication, and emotional connection.

**Tutorial** — Small group session where a tutor clarifies doubts, reviews assignments, and extends classroom learning.

**Laboratory method** — Hands-on experimental learning. Essential in science, engineering, and health sciences. Develops observation and inquiry skills.

**Fieldwork / field trip** — Learning in a real-world environment outside the classroom (geography surveys, archaeological sites, industrial visits).

**Workshop** — Short, intensive, hands-on session focused on a specific skill.

**Internship / practicum** — Extended work experience in a professional setting. Integrates theory with practice.

