### Part C — Other Important Concepts

**Flipped Classroom** — A blended approach where students watch pre-recorded lectures at home (online) and use classroom time for discussions, problem-solving, and activities (learner-centred). It flips the traditional homework/lecture structure.

**Blended Learning** — Combination of online and offline methods. Students get the flexibility of online learning with the support of face-to-face interaction. Also called hybrid learning.

**Heuristic Method** — Students discover knowledge themselves through investigation. Teacher guides but does not reveal. Based on the principle "learning by doing." Coined by H.E. Armstrong.

**Inquiry-based learning** — Students pose questions, investigate, and construct knowledge. Close to heuristic method but more structured.

